{title: Multiple Delegate Sections}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]This song has [C]multiple
[D]Delegate sections [G]embedded
{end_of_verse}

{comment: ABC notation for the melody}
{start_of_abc}
X:1
T:Main Theme
M:4/4
L:1/8
K:G
| G2 B2 d2 B2 | A2 c2 e2 c2 |
| d2 B2 G2 B2 | A4 G4 |
{end_of_abc}

{start_of_chorus}
[C]Multiple [G]formats
[D]In one [G]song
{end_of_chorus}

{comment: Lilypond for the harmony}
{start_of_ly}
\relative c' {
  \time 4/4
  \key g \major
  g4 b d g |
  fis4 a c fis |
  e4 d b g |
  a2 g2 |
}
{end_of_ly}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G]Mixing delegate [C]types freely
[D]Each rendered by its [G]own engine
{end_of_verse}

{comment: SVG decoration}
{start_of_svg}
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="100" height="20">
  <line x1="0" y1="10" x2="100" y2="10" stroke="black" stroke-width="1"/>
</svg>
{end_of_svg}

{start_of_textblock}
Final Notes:
This song demonstrates that multiple delegate
environments can coexist in a single ChordPro file.
Each is processed by its respective handler.
{end_of_textblock}
